div.p: Three methods with fallback logic for enabling the A20 address line

ul.li: May not work on all systems

div.p: asm in al, 0x92 or al, 2 ; Set A20 bit and al, 0xFE ; Clear reset out 0x92, al

asm ; Wait for input buffer empty wait1: in al, 0x64 test al, 2 jnz wait1 ; Send read command mov al, 0xD0 out 0x64, al ; Read output port wait2: in al, 0x64 test al, 1 jz wait2 in al, 0x60 ; Set A20 bit and write back or al, 2 mov ah, al mov al, 0xD1 out 0x64, al

ol.li: If A20 disabled: both map to same physical address (wraparound)
If A20 enabled: different physical addresses, values differ
Return 1 if different (A20 on), 0 if same (A20 off)
